  - TextHeading: Controls (summary)
    TextSubheading: 
    TextBody: "Menus: Move + PlaceBomb as confirm. Arena: WASD/arrows, Space bomb, Tab switch Bomberman/FPS, Esc/P/Start pause. FPS: legacy Input Manager — WASD, mouse, LMB/RMB, Shift sprint, Space jump (in FPS mode). See README.md for full tables."
    LinkName: 
    LinkUrl: 
    PingObjectName: 
    PingObjectGuid: 
    MenuItemName: 
    MenuItemPath: 
  - TextHeading: Known issues
    TextSubheading: 
    TextBody: Alternate level stub in GameManager; ContinueOnAnyInput double-advance; music not replaced as intended (commercial release would risk copyright); mobile overlay and D-pad issues unresolved; ML/arena AI implemented but weak. Optional dev packages (Netcode, ML-Agents, MCP) not required for a local build. See README.md for full list.
    LinkName: 
    LinkUrl: 
    PingObjectName: 
    PingObjectGuid: 
    MenuItemName: 
    MenuItemPath: 
  - TextHeading: Third-party assets
    TextSubheading: 
    TextBody: Full package table and embedded assets are listed in README.md at the project root. This project also uses the com.rmc.rmc-readme package for this in-editor Read Me.
    LinkName: 
    LinkUrl: 
    PingObjectName: 
    PingObjectGuid: 
    MenuItemName: 
    MenuItemPath: 
  - TextHeading: Generative AI
    TextSubheading: 
    TextBody: "Cursor, Google Gemini (concept art), Clipchamp (AI-assisted pitch script + Ryan TTS voiceover), and Unity MCP (development only). See README.md — Generative AI disclosure — for full tools table, workflow, Cursor plan excerpt, and Gemini prompts. Coding habits: .cursor/skills/unity-skill/SKILL.md."
    LinkName: 
    LinkUrl: 
    PingObjectName: 
    PingObjectGuid: 
    MenuItemName: 
    MenuItemPath: 
  - TextHeading: References
    TextSubheading: 
    TextBody: "Edit REFERENCES.md at the repo root. Sync into README.md with python tools/sync_readme_references.py or when building the PDF (python tools/generate_readme_pdf.py)."
    LinkName: 
    LinkUrl: 
    PingObjectName: 
    PingObjectGuid: 
    MenuItemName: 
    MenuItemPath: 
